00:46:03.080 --> 00:46:04.976
TIA KANSARA HON FRIBA:
Where did the time go?

00:46:04.976 --> 00:46:07.530
AUDIENCE: I was very
interested in the index

00:46:07.530 --> 00:46:09.470
you were talking about.

00:46:09.470 --> 00:46:12.410
And I was wondering if, when
you took to, I don't know,

00:46:12.410 --> 00:46:18.605
[INAUDIBLE] or
even annually could

00:46:18.605 --> 00:46:20.275
help implement this index.

00:46:20.275 --> 00:46:22.183
Is there a company
in the world that

00:46:22.183 --> 00:46:23.900
is interested in doing this?

00:46:23.900 --> 00:46:26.840
Is it something that looks
completely idealistic

00:46:26.840 --> 00:46:28.800
and is never going to happen?

00:46:28.800 --> 00:46:31.740
And [INAUDIBLE] to happen.

00:46:31.740 --> 00:46:37.125
[INAUDIBLE] So what's
the state of this?

00:46:37.125 --> 00:46:39.250
TIA KANSARA HON FRIBA: It's
a really good question.

00:46:39.250 --> 00:46:43.630
So Bhutan, this year,
launched the GNH business.

00:46:43.630 --> 00:46:46.060
Bhutan introduced the
Gross National Happiness

00:46:46.060 --> 00:46:47.860
index in the 1970s.

00:46:47.860 --> 00:46:51.100
And wanted to understand what if
the economy wasn't about money,

00:46:51.100 --> 00:46:52.462
but it was about well-being?.

00:46:52.462 --> 00:46:54.670
And so they started to
explore this whole well-being.

00:46:54.670 --> 00:47:00.970
And I think it was 1970s onwards
is when, every three years, all

00:47:00.970 --> 00:47:03.310
of this data was
collected to show

00:47:03.310 --> 00:47:06.500
what was the state of
well-being in their country.

00:47:06.500 --> 00:47:09.550
And then what they did was to
explore a happiness report.

00:47:09.550 --> 00:47:12.160
And I think you may be aware
that many other countries

00:47:12.160 --> 00:47:13.576
around the world
have been looking

00:47:13.576 --> 00:47:16.120
at well-being, British
government being one of them.

00:47:16.120 --> 00:47:18.370
The UAE has been talking
about well-being as well,

00:47:18.370 --> 00:47:20.830
happiness ministers,
very interesting sort

00:47:20.830 --> 00:47:23.800
of understanding and
appreciation of well-being.

00:47:23.800 --> 00:47:26.941
Another thing that they've
recently launched last year,

00:47:26.941 --> 00:47:29.440
a couple of years ago they did
the Gross National Happiness,

00:47:29.440 --> 00:47:30.610
seventh conference.

00:47:30.610 --> 00:47:32.980
Or sixth conference-- this
year it was the seventh.

00:47:32.980 --> 00:47:35.980
And they said, what if
businesses were also

00:47:35.980 --> 00:47:37.534
aligned with this?

00:47:37.534 --> 00:47:39.075
And they said, OK,
well, you're going

00:47:39.075 --> 00:47:41.449
to be introducing this to
businesses already and probably

00:47:41.449 --> 00:47:42.940
taking a top down approach.

00:47:42.940 --> 00:47:45.130
They took 40
different businesses

00:47:45.130 --> 00:47:48.250
and asked them whether they were
approaching their businesses

00:47:48.250 --> 00:47:51.220
with the kind of well-being
index within the context

00:47:51.220 --> 00:47:53.890
of the products and services
and the employees that

00:47:53.890 --> 00:47:58.580
work there, kind of, like,
the organizational structure.

00:47:58.580 --> 00:48:02.390
And when this came
out, one of the things

00:48:02.390 --> 00:48:04.850
that I suggested to the
Bhutanese [INAUDIBLE]

00:48:04.850 --> 00:48:07.417
but also their team at the
center of Bhutanese studies

00:48:07.417 --> 00:48:08.750
was you're doing the well-being.

00:48:08.750 --> 00:48:11.750
Why don't you also do the
environmental side of it, too?

00:48:11.750 --> 00:48:15.470
So if you were to, like B corps,
analyze the whole business

00:48:15.470 --> 00:48:17.690
and the impact that it had
on the environment as well

00:48:17.690 --> 00:48:20.150
as the well-being, what kind
of a metric would you have?

00:48:20.150 --> 00:48:22.160
You'd be the first in
the world to do it.

00:48:22.160 --> 00:48:24.200
So we're exploring
that together.

00:48:24.200 --> 00:48:25.120
It's funny, actually.

00:48:25.120 --> 00:48:27.010
You know, at the
beginning of the year

00:48:27.010 --> 00:48:29.660
when I was writing
the convergence of AI

00:48:29.660 --> 00:48:32.944
and ecology piece, I watched all
of the "Black Mirror" series.

00:48:32.944 --> 00:48:34.610
I don't know if you've
come across that.

00:48:34.610 --> 00:48:35.450
It was so much fun.

00:48:35.450 --> 00:48:36.724
I loved it.

00:48:36.724 --> 00:48:38.390
And one of the things
that I came across

00:48:38.390 --> 00:48:42.470
was, if I could write
a piece for the future,

00:48:42.470 --> 00:48:46.380
like 40 years, maybe even 30 or
10 years, of how this could be.

00:48:46.380 --> 00:48:48.110
I went a bit crazy
and I wrote that.

00:48:48.110 --> 00:48:52.100
It then became the preliminary
piece for the "Medium" article.

00:48:52.100 --> 00:48:55.820
But one of the things that I
wrote was, in two years' time--

00:48:55.820 --> 00:48:57.680
and I wrote it as if
I was looking back.

00:48:57.680 --> 00:49:01.260
So two years ago, this
suggestion was made.

00:49:01.260 --> 00:49:05.900
And then this was implemented at
the government level in Bhutan.

00:49:05.900 --> 00:49:07.970
And it's interesting how
that is happening now.

00:49:07.970 --> 00:49:10.580
And I wonder if because
that intention was there,

00:49:10.580 --> 00:49:12.905
that something like this
has actually manifested.

00:49:12.905 --> 00:49:15.380
I have a very interesting
relationship with intuition

00:49:15.380 --> 00:49:16.700
and manifestation.

00:49:16.700 --> 00:49:18.770
But many different
countries around the world

00:49:18.770 --> 00:49:21.200
from a government level are
trying to introduce this.

00:49:21.200 --> 00:49:25.160
Like in Goa, with the
installation they suggested--

00:49:25.160 --> 00:49:29.970
2019-- what about if we had
a festival on zero waste?

00:49:29.970 --> 00:49:33.360
Funny, because the festival that
we had this art installation

00:49:33.360 --> 00:49:36.900
for a year ago, I suggested, how
about if we have our festival,

00:49:36.900 --> 00:49:38.400
a zero waste festival?

00:49:38.400 --> 00:49:41.670
And they said, well, why
don't you do it first,

00:49:41.670 --> 00:49:45.060
and then we'll see how, from
the evaluation, we could do it.

00:49:45.060 --> 00:49:47.910
And it's funny that the
government is now suggesting--

00:49:47.910 --> 00:49:49.410
completely unrelated,
the government

00:49:49.410 --> 00:49:51.600
is suggesting we have
like zero waste festival.

00:49:51.600 --> 00:49:53.820
But I think there
are pockets of people

00:49:53.820 --> 00:49:56.020
coming together and doing
very interesting things.

00:49:56.020 --> 00:49:58.890
But for the World
Replenish Index

00:49:58.890 --> 00:50:01.312
at MIT last year in
December, I launched

00:50:01.312 --> 00:50:03.270
something called the
Replenish Business Canvas.

00:50:03.270 --> 00:50:07.780
And I wanted to suggest that,
if every single startup, not

00:50:07.780 --> 00:50:09.949
[INAUDIBLE] company,
come to the end of it,

00:50:09.949 --> 00:50:11.490
and now I've got
some money, I'll put

00:50:11.490 --> 00:50:12.836
some money towards [INAUDIBLE].

00:50:12.836 --> 00:50:14.502
Uh huh.

00:50:14.502 --> 00:50:15.960
Right at the
beginning, when you're

00:50:15.960 --> 00:50:17.850
formulating your
company, you could

00:50:17.850 --> 00:50:21.360
say that this company is going
to be a zero waste company.

00:50:21.360 --> 00:50:23.400
And where am I going
to get materials from?

00:50:23.400 --> 00:50:27.480
So right at inception, you could
introduce this whole idea--

00:50:27.480 --> 00:50:30.750
what kind of businesses
would we have in the future?

00:50:30.750 --> 00:50:32.970
And I'm surprised, but
even at Harvard and MIT,

00:50:32.970 --> 00:50:35.910
both of their MBA programs, as
well as Oxford Said business

00:50:35.910 --> 00:50:38.190
school, do not have
enough case studies

00:50:38.190 --> 00:50:41.320
of businesses that have done
extremely well in this field.

00:50:41.320 --> 00:50:43.680
So that's one of the projects
within the World Replenish

00:50:43.680 --> 00:50:47.220
Index, to build on the case
studies of business model

00:50:47.220 --> 00:50:51.690
innovation of where businesses
have done it, have made it.

00:50:51.690 --> 00:50:53.580
So it's a lot of work.

00:50:53.580 --> 00:50:56.069
And I need a lot of help.

00:50:56.069 --> 00:50:57.360
Maybe some of you will help me.

